<br>
It didn't matter. All that really mattered at all was that the sun was hot. The letters were gruff, and the sweat from the heat made it hard to read the letters, but they were still there. He didn't know why he knew what they said, but he knew. &quot;B  O  B&quot; was engraved into his hard, rock-colored flesh. His tan wasn't the darkest thing on the lad's body, though. His hair was blacker than coal- well, actually, it kind of *was* coal, as he'd just emerged from a deep mine in the near past. His fingernails were long and dirty, his hair matted to his leathery back. He should have been dressed in a loincloth, for all the difference it would make.<br>
<br>
Actually, when he looked down, he was surprised to see pants at all. Tattered and torn at the knees, the denim was stone washed and faded. Bob really was confused, now.<br>
<br>
The night did little to aid Bob's sweating. He was still covered in a sheen, but at least that made the dirt and soil come off easier when he took a dunk in a small watering hole.<br>
<br>
A scream.<br>
<br>
Of all the things he couldn't remember, Bob could remember the sound of a woman. He could also remember the distinct scent of blood. He could taste it in the air once again. Through the dimly lit streets and shady, forested areas, Bob took off at full flight. Females meant more of his kind. It had to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/9/02 10:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sorry if it sucks, you caught me just as i was going to bed</span><hr size=1> <br>
The whip comes down hard over and over again on the girls delicate aqua skin. Her screams die out along with her consciousness. They would not let her escape her harsh reality. A swift kick to the stomach returns her to the world and to the unbareable pain. Had there been anything in her stomach, it would had been on the ground in front of her, however a lack of food for three days made that impossible. Slashes in the back of her shirt reveal the steadily emerald blood that bleeds from her newly made cuts that rest atop scars. A man yanks her from the ground and shoves her back in line with the rest of them, the rest of her people. Their lives were some of the most difficult to live. They would work out in the fields all day until they could lift their arms no more, for that they would be beat just like the girl was. Each one of dorned the same three letters on their arm, though none of them were literate enough to read. The progretion of slaves goes on into the distance, there was hundreds of them, all going towards the same dreaded place...<br>
<br>
Tears stream down the girls nearly flawless face and clear two small pathways down her cheeks. Had she been clean, her aqua skin would have glittered in the light, but she was covered in dirt from the dusty fields. Blisters on her hands throb as a light wind rushes past her. She can feel the pain taking over and threatening collapse. The wind rushes through her frosty hair and swirls around her. Everything begins to spin. Falling to the ground, her violet eyes blur. The last thing seen is the Slave Master's whip rising into the air above her. <br>
