<br>
Below the long leather tail gripped in his hand was a beautiful woman. Young, yes, but she was definetley grown into womanhood. There was something else odd about her, as well... What was it?<br>
<br>
Was it the blood gushing from her body? Was it the dust that covered her, the way her body sprawled across the ground with exhaustion? Was it her tightly contracted muscles, obviously developed from long hours of hard work? No. Just before the beauty fell to the ground, &quot;B  O  B&quot; knew what it was; the eyes. Her beautiful, violet eyes shone with the radiance of a world gone mad, and &quot;B  O  B&quot; couldn't let that look go. Then the whip was raised.<br>
<br>
He didn't know anything about his abilities. &quot;B  O  B&quot; didn't think anything about the way he was able to nearly instantly appear beneath the fall of the wicked, barbed weapon. All he knew was that he needed to be there, and he was.<br>
<br>
The astounded Slave Master nearly screeched in rage. He ripped the whip back off of Bob's arm, taking flesh and sinew with it. He seemed not to notice. Muscled thugs crowded in around Bob, outnumbering him four to one, including the Slave Master. The wild, ragged looking young man ran dirty fingernails through his hair, and growled. Everything changed from it's normal hue, a violet tint, to a vicious red glow. Blood pumped through his tightly corded muscles, and a howl escaped his throat. A fist came screaming towards Bob's face, and he leaned backwards to avoid it. Bending at his knees, the fist overshot. He continued his backwards descent when the whip shot towards him. It caught Bob in the abdomen, just above the navel, and he grabbed the barbed strip of leather again. This time, Bob braced himself on the ground with a palm down, and yanked with all his strength. The Slave Master tumbled over.<br>
<br>
Three more standing. Bob hopped into the air and spun, releasing his hold on the length of the whip to send it spiraling outwards from his body. The barbs caught one man in the chest, another across the face, and the third avoided it all together. Bob landed, kicking up a cloud of dust, and was distracted from his melee by a stirring near his feet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 11:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> la~</span><hr size=1> Everything was in a haze. The world still spun around her, but she could make out figures. One stood before her, looking down with eyes that comforted her. He was a model for perfection with his deeply tanned skin and jet-black hair. She was caught up in his gaze when she saw it. A large man coming up fast to strike down the one who was obviously helping her. Instincts kick in and she raises her palms to the on commer. Closing her eyes and turning her face away, she takes a deep breath and prepairs for the worst. Voilet strands of energy explode from her palms and completely shoot through the man. Without warning he falls to his knees, his eyes gone violet and blood seeping from his mouth. Fear stuck to her body, she could not move or open her eyes. She heard movement near her, but she was already gone. Lost in her own mind with the 'darkness' encircling her. Her body trembles and her breath is taken in gasps, ~let the whip come... oh god let it come... the pain will save me... let the whip come...~ The whip never came... but the tears seem to never stop flowing... <p><Br> <Br> <Br>I'm just a sample of a soul made to look just like a human being</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 12:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: la~</span><hr size=1> The violet waves pierced through the man's skin. Bob had broken the man's nose who avoided the whip. The one with a gash on his chest was grapling with the smaller wild man, but that third, the one with a gash on his face, died first. Instinct drew Bob's body out of the way of the blast, and the man he didn't see fell dead.<br>
<br>
He quickly bit out the gashed chest man's windpipe, and mule kicked the other one's face. His head spun around with a resounding *PPOPPP!*, and Bob wiped his mouth off. He knelt down to the beautiful woman, only now seeing her beautiful, aqua skin. Her eyes were clenched tight, face caked in dirt while tears streamed down, clearing chaotic paths across her perfect face. Bob put his hand on her cheek, and lifted her head, making cheek to cheek contact. Beauty... Power... Wasted? No... Come to me, he thought. Come back with me...<br>
<br>
The red faded. Blue serenity replaced the previous red viciousness. A tear fell from his cheek for this tortured being, this battered soul. He knew not how, or how long it took, but Bob was suddenly kneeling, resting her back on green grass next to a small stream. The clear water shone through, and he poured a bit on her aqua face. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 12:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: la~</span><hr size=1> She felt it, the cool water against her skin, and disappeared. It had been forever since she had returned to the water, her abilities kept her from it while living as a slave. She was able to change forms and become part of the water, doing so always gave her mental clarity and a peace that she found no where else. She let only a moment pass before stepping out of the water and next to the man who saved her. Her skin was clean and glimmered like it should. Her hair was straight and seemed longer now that the tangles were gone. Her clothes had changed. She now wore long white pants, and a white top that had no straps and showed her stomach. She kneels down next to the man and stares into his eyes, completely lost. Was she dreaming? Was he real? Feeling embarassed for no apparent reason she looks down. Her voice is small and hushed, barely rising to a whipser, &quot;Thank you...&quot;  <p><Br> <Br> <Br>I'm just a sample of a soul made to look just like a human being</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% v