<br>
Bob spoke, shakily, not trusting his own voice. It was still gutteral and a bit rough, but he could make out words well enough, to convey emotions, if nothing else. The violet tint returned to his world as Bob looked into this creature's eyes. So beautiful...<br>
<br>
&quot;F...&quot; He began. Looking around, he saw a yellow daisy. The flower was common everywhere, but there was only one here; Bob didn't know the worthlessness of this blossom, but the feeling was conveyed well enough. &quot;F-f...&quot; He handed the flower to the being before him. He knew he'd not find another creature so striking and so compassionate on this mudball of a planet; not among his kind, nor hers. Well, if there was truly a difference between the two. &quot;Frrrr...&quot;<br>
<br>
Setting the flower into her palm, Bob nearly choked on the words. &quot;B-beeee myyy... Frrrr... frrrrrrrrrRRRRRRE- frrriend?&quot; Large violet eyes looked down at him, and seemed to glow in the tint of the world.<br>
<br>
&quot;Be my frrrrriend?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 12:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> da~</span><hr size=1> Friend? Friend. He wanted to be her friend? Why? She never had had a friend before... ~I wonder what a friend would be like...~ Looking down at the flower, she admires it's beauty. Twirling it between her thumb and pointer finger, she lets her mind trail off on the thought of a friend. Tears sting the back of her eyelids, someone wanted to be her friend... <br>
<br>
&quot;I... I... I...&quot;  What could she say? What words would be right? Interaction with other life was so difficult. She begins to wish she was back in line... back where she knew what to do, where she was asure of herself. <br>
<br>
&quot;I... I... I... I... I'm... sorry&quot; Letting the flower drop to the ground, she hugs her knees to her chest and burries her face. Back in line... Back in line... Back in line... Back in line.. <p><Br> <Br> <Br>I'm just a sample of a soul made to look just like a human being</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 8:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: da~</span><hr size=1> The flower nearly hit the ground before Bob scooped it up. He looked at it closely, inspecting for damage. Then, he saw it; there was a BUG on his FLOWER!! Grunting angrily, he dunked the dandelion into the water, and watched the frail insect float away on crystalline waters.<br>
<br>
Setting a knuckle down and hunching his already crooked spine, Bob did a kind of monkey jigg over towards her. He put a dingy arm around her shoulders, and tucked the flower behind her ear. Tears stung at the edges of his eyes. She didn't want to be my friend...<br>
<br>
Bob didn't waste any time. A reassuring nuzzle on the delicate skin of her arm, and he was gone like the breeze. Before she even looked up, he was grunting and hooting with each leap. He was into the trees, russling the branches before she realized he was gone-<br>
<br>
After all, what's not a friend is an enemy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 9:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sleep is needed for a clear mind.maybe thats why my mind isn</span><hr size=1> This time, her tears would end. As they did she knew what she was to say to this well-hearted stranger, but he was no where in sight. Again, she had done it again. As if forcing her whole family away from her was not enough, she had to force someone who helped her away as well. Someone... who helped her, that was right! She had to find him. Instantly her eyes shift aqua, where was he? Her eyes were drawn upwards, the trees. All that she saw was a blur, green energies radiated from the tree's, but this kind soul radiated yellow, he was easy to follow. She had not noticed, but clouds formed over head while the two had talked, or in this case, while they did not talk. Slowly, one drop after another fell to the ground and was absorbed instantly into the thirsty soil. Her feet moved faster and faster along the softening ground, following that yellow energy where ever it took her. With her own speed, the rain fell harder. Sheets of rain drop from the heavens, it was time to use her skill to her advantage. Mid-stride she jumps, and disappears. Faster than any human could ever hope to travel, her form liquifies and is sent rushing from one droplet to the next, she *would* catch up to this person, she had to...  <p><Br> <Br> <Br>I'm just a sample of a soul made to look just like a human being</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 9:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wablop.</span><hr size=1> Instinct played out again. Bob could feel this presence behind him- he's not sure how, but he knew it. He didn't know what it was, but he knew it followed him.<br>
<br>
Things don't follow things unless they're hunting them.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hunt-   errrrrrr!!!&quot; he growled. His eyes glowed green, and everything about him turned to that of the trees- he blended in like a chameleon. At first, he was surprised by this. Soon after, though, he felt the presence of the stalker pass him by, underneath the canopy. POUNCE!<br>
<br>
On the way down, his eyes flared red. Combat magick seeped from his pores, and red flares of energy flowed from his body, streaming outwards to encase the thing that followed. Only....<br>
<br>
There was nothing there!<br>
<br>
Confused and bewildered, Bob knew he felt the presence before him, but there was nothing...<br>
<br>
The drops sluiced off his body- dirt was slowly washed away as he stared where he knew something should be. He sat down, the red fading, his eyes shifting back to violet; the shrubs surrounding him and trees above him did little to protect him from the chill of the rain. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 12:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> mwahaha</span><hr size=1> She appears, her form perfect as ever and completely dry. In her hand was a white cloak. A shy and half forced smile plays on her lips as she looks at Bob.<br>
