Three eight nine three two dash fifty-nine SC4. That was the only thing she was called by. The numbers were printed on her arm, well, burned there anyways. &quot;38932-59 SC4&quot; Her code number. Slaves never were given names, that would make them too human, too alive. Of all the things she could call herself... what would she tell him was her name? She never had heard any names before... <br>
<br>
&quot;I... I don't have a name...&quot; She looks down shamefully, her eyes dark with embarrassment. No name, how great. The one time she met someone, they wanted to know the one thing she could not tell them. Three eight nine three two dash fifty-nine SC4... her name, her identity, her restraint. <p><Br> <Br> <Br>I'm just a sample of a soul made to look just like a human being</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Name</span><hr size=1> &quot;Err tu' le grotto del as'ahmay, mien dellagroot del ne'seeko,&quot;<br>
~&quot;You are a vision of beauty, my princess of the waves,&quot;~<br>
<br>
The speech came so fast that Bob couldn't understand what he said. All he knew was that the common language was coming from some external force- the tongue he spoke in, which he somehow *knew* was called Combine, came from him, indeed.<br>
<br>
His eyes lifted from the ground to meet hers; she was a bit bewildered, and Bob wasn't sure if she understood. Somehow, for the first time, he did. Being slightly taller than her, he could stoop a bit, as was his normal posture. Bob touched her shoulder, saying, &quot;Mien dellagroot del ne'seeko,&quot;<br>
                       &quot;My princess of the waves,&quot;<br>
<br>
The transparent voice encased his words again, clarifying them. Bob took her stamped and numbered wrist, and put his lips to it. Then he pointed to himself again. &quot;Bob.&quot;<br>
<br>
He pointed to her. &quot;As'ahmay,&quot; he whispered.<br>
                          &quot;Beauty,&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 8:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> As'ahmay</span><hr size=1> &quot;As'ahmay...&quot; <br>
